<taxonomicName authority="Machado, 1945" authorityName="Machado" authorityYear="1945" box="[151,535,546,572]" class="Reptilia" family="Boidae" genus="Epicrates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="assisi">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,337,546,572]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Epicrates assisi</emphasis>
Machado, 
<number box="[476,535,546,572]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="1945.0">1945</number>
</taxonomicName>
“Salamanta, Cobra-arco-íris”
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,915,546,606]" box="[151,370,581,606]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">(Figs. 9.4 and 22.2)</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,653,858]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Caatinga endemic species. There are records for this species in all portions of the Caatinga. It is distributed in areas from sea level to 
<quantity box="[354,427,690,714]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.83" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="m" value="983.0">983 m</quantity>
elevation. It inhabits all phytophisiognomies of the Caatinga and was recorded recently also in the Atlantic Forest domain near the coast, perhaps as a result of secondary dispersion due to the deforestation of these areas (P. Passos, pers. comm.). It is simpatric with 
<taxonomicName box="[982,1099,762,785]" class="Reptilia" family="Boidae" genus="Epicrates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="crassus">
<emphasis box="[982,1099,762,785]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">E. crassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in north Minas Gerais, in the Cerrado-Caatinga contact area (
<bibRefCitation author="Passos" box="[510,809,797,822]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refString="Passos, P. &amp; Fernandes, R. (2008) Revision of the Epicrates cenchria complex (Serpentes: Boidae). Herpetological Monographs, 22, 1 - 30. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1655 / 06 - 003.1" type="journal article" year="2008">
Passos &amp; Fernandes 
<number box="[748,809,798,822]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). It has semi-arboreal habits, is nocturnal, and feeds on vertebrates (
<bibRefCitation author="Guedes" box="[288,442,833,858]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refString="Guedes, T. B. (2006) Estrutura da comunidade de serpentes de uma area de caatinga do nordeste brasileiro. Unpublished MSThesis, Universidade Federal do Rio Grande do Norte, Natal, 76 pp." type="book" year="2006">
Guedes 
<number box="[381,442,833,858]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
